news.title: Delhi: 64,000 illegal constructions identified in past seven years
news.para: The ministry said while the Municipal Corporation of Delhi (MCD) and New Delhi Municipal Council (NDMC) have given data from 2016 onwards, the STF started the detection of illegal and unauthorised constructions from 2018 when it was set up.

news.title: Shriram Properties' sales bookings rises 26% to Rs 313 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: ​The Bengaluru-based company, in a statement, said that its sales bookings in volume terms rose 20 per cent to 0.66 million square feet in the first quarter of 2022-23 fiscal from 0.55 million square feet in the year-ago period.

news.title: Gujarat Land Grab act crackdown on encroachers
news.para: ​The circular ordering the imposition of the act has also directed district collectors to ensure that civic services and electricity are denied with immediate effect to commercial or industrial units that have come up on government plots.

news.title: Apartment to get costlier to rent for corporate executives
news.para: Renting an apartment by a registered entity will now attract an 18% Goods and Services Tax (GST) as per the recommendations.

news.title: SC appointed panel suggests property relief measures in Chandigarh
news.para: An action taken report submitted by the administration before the Supreme Court, in which the committee’s recommendations were also part, mentioned these measures.

news.title: Noida: Call on audit of buildings near Supertech twin towers left to CBRI
news.para: Noida Authority chief architect and town planner Ishtiyaq Ahmed said if the CBRI give an opinion in favour of a structural audit, Supertech, the developer of Emerald Court, would have to get it done by a reputable consultant and submit a report.

news.title: DDA must register real estate projects with regulator: Delhi-RERA chairman
news.para: And if they do not get registered with Delhi-RERA, Kumar said the authority has got enough power to take action against them under sections 59 and 61 of the Act.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco puts CRZ plot for sale, environmentalists write to CMO
news.para: The chief minister's office (CMO) has directed the UD and environment departments to look into this matter following the complaint.

news.title: Nashik civic body to give tenancy documents to tenants of dilapidated wadas
news.para: There are over 1,000 dilapidated wadas across six divisions of the city and majority of them are in Nashik East and Panchavati divisions. Also, the condition of around 70 strcutures is dangerous.

news.title: Simpliwork Offices leases 1.5 lakh sq ft space from DLF, Mindspace in Chennai
news.para: ​Bengaluru-based Simpliwork Offices, which provides managed office space to corporates, has taken on lease about 80,000 square feet from DLF and around 70,000 square feet from Mindspace.

news.title: Chandigarh: Need-based changes panel report call on July 26
news.para: Allottees of the CHB were likely to get some relief as a slew of relaxations have been recommended by the committee that was constituted to study requests to allow further need-based changes in residential units.

news.title: House introduces land grab bill in Goa assembly
news.para: The first empowers authorities investigating land grabbing cases by allowing them to file a case before the appropriate court or tribunal to determine the veracity of any document, and within two days of the court’s order declaring the document forged, the officer must revert the land to its original owner.

news.title: Government mulls proposal seeking extension of PMAY-Urban scheme by two years
news.para: ​In a written reply to a question on Monday, Minister of State for Housing and Urban Affairs Kaushal Kishore said that meanwhile, an interim extension of six months for all verticals, except Credit Linked Subsidy Scheme, has been granted.

news.title: Delhi court orders release of Sushil, Gopal Ansal in evidence tampering case
news.para: While modifying the magisterial court's order on sentence, the District Judge on Tuesday also ordered the release of former court staff Dinesh Chand Sharma and Ansal's then employee P P Batra against their already undergone jail term since November 8.

news.title: Ex-promoters influenced DHFL's share price, paid builder high fee: CBI
news.para: The chargesheet filed ag-ainst the Wadhawans, builder Sanjay Chhabria, Yes Bank founder Rana Kapoor and others claimed that they entered into a criminal conspiracy causing loss to Yes Bank and DHFL for personal gain.
